    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA model ensemble achieves Medium assurance level for prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct intended for thoracolumbar fixation. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given the standardized single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 and the robustness of the multi-laboratory experimental evidence base. Overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission use.",
